Author: STUDHOLME
Vol / Page: 183
Edition: 1954
Quote: The wool was sent to Napier. For the first part of the journey over the hills it was carried by pack horses - sixty-two of them - each taking about 150 lb. in what were called `pockets' - long shaped packs slung one on each side of the saddle.
